    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Optical devices for use with both eyes consisting of two small telescopes fitted together side by side on a single frame and containing an erecting system usually with both focusing tubes simultaneously adjustable by means of a single screw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Optische apparaten die voor beide ogen worden gehouden en bestaan uit twee smalle telescopen die door middel van een frame aan elkaar vastzitten en voorzien zijn van een systeem waarmee meestal beide kijkglazen tegelijk kunnen worden scherpgesteld door middel van een schroef.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>為一種供雙眼使用的光學裝置，在單一鏡架上包含兩個比鄰且組裝在一起的小型單筒望遠鏡，並包含一個直立結構。通常具有兩個對焦管，可同時經由單一螺桿調整焦距。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Optische Vorrichtung zum Gebrauch mit beiden Augen, bestehend aus zwei kleinen Fernrohren, die in einem einzelnen Gestell nebeneinander zusammengefügt sind und ein Montagesystem beinhalten, mit dem gewöhnlich beide Fokussierrohre mittels einer einzelnen Schraube gleichzeitig einstellbar sind.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Strumenti ottici che sfruttano la visione binoculare, costituiti da un insieme ben accoppiato di due cannocchiali identici incernierati parallelamente ad un cardine centrale meccanico che permette di poter regolare in modo facile, preciso e veloce la corretta distanza interpupillare per ogni utente.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122289/Thesaurus Nuovo soggettario [online] (2025-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
